Punica (Poenica, compare munio, moenia): a word kindred with Phoenician.—Tyri08, Agenoris: added to explain Punica, of which AEneas could be expected to know nothing, as well as to indicate a civilized race; hence sed in the next verse. Agenor was father of Cadmus and Europa, and founder of Sidon, the metropolis of Tyre. The lands, however, are not Phoenician, but Libyan. -
